      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. to make the drama feel more real, i want to add some conflict. sometimes in movies, these scenes go from being happy to being really intense really fast. for a family like this, do you think the tension would mostly come from things like religious differences, or maybe stuff like money and struggle? like, if they're having a hard time making ends meet, how does that usually play out at the dinner table?",
